.TH "ptep_notify" 9 "ptep_notify" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
ptep_notify \- call all invalidation callbacks for a specific pte.
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "void" ptep_notify
.BI "(struct mm_struct *mm "  ","
.BI "unsigned long vmaddr "  ","
.BI "pte_t *pte "  ","
.BI "unsigned long bits "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "mm" 12
pointer to the process mm_struct
.IP "vmaddr" 12
-- undescribed --
.IP "pte" 12
pointer to the page table entry
.IP "bits" 12
bits from the pgste that caused the notify call
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
This function is assumed to be called with the page table lock held
for the pte to notify.
